    <note type="biography">
        <p>Nonconformist divine and geologist. Taught geology, mathematics, Hebrew, and Old Testament exegesis, 1869–75, and wrote "Minerals of the Bible" (an article in Cassell’s <hi rend="italic">Bible educator</hi>) and the address "Cosmical theories of the earth". He admired CD’s achievements while disagreeing with his theories.</p></note>
